						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to the 16th century on palaeography grounds.</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of three <hi rend="italic">rūkas</hi> in the from of taxes on marriages among the Balija śeṭṭis to donate the same to temple of Bhīmēśvara probably in presence of mahānāḍu (assembly).</p>						

						</summary>
